<li>1 Abbreviations used are : AdoCbl , adenosylcobalamin ; AdoCbi , adenosylcobinamide ; AdoCbi-P , adenosylcobinamide phosphate ; AdoCbi-GDP , adenosylcobinamide guanosine diphosphate ; Cbi , cobinamide ; ( CN ) 2Cbi , dicyanocobinamide ; ( CN ) 2Cbi-P , dicyanocobinamide phosphate ; ( CN ) 2Cbi ¬ GDP , dicyanocobinamide guanosine diphosphate ; GuoCbi , guanosylcobinamide ; InoCbi , inosylcobinamide ; CyoCbi , cytosylcobinamide ; dAdoCbi , 2 ' ,5 ' - dideoxyadenosylcobinamide ; ATP , adenosine triphosphate ; GTP , guanosine triphosphate ; dATP , 2 ' - deoxyadenosine triphosphate ; dGTP , 2 ' - deoxyadenosine triphosphate ; CTP , cytosine triphosphate ; dCTP , 2 ' - deoxycytosine triphosphate ; GMP , guanosine monophosphate ; AMP , adenosine monophosphate ; NMP , nucleoside monophosphate ; AP , R-1-amino-O-2-propanol ; AP-P , R-1-amino-propanol-O-2-phosphate ; DTT , dithiothreitol ; PMSF , phenylmethanesulfonyl fluoride ; EDTA , ethylenediaminetetracetic acid ; TLC , thin layer chromatography ; HPLC , high performance liquid chromatography ; BSA , bovine serum albumin ; TCA , DEAE , hydrochloride ; Tris ( 2-carboxyethyl ) phosphine TCEP-HCl , acid ; trichloroacetic diethylaminoethyl , Tris , Tris ( hycroxylmethyl ) aminomethane .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10869342" target="_blank">10869342</a>]<br></li>
<li>Abbreviations used are as follows : Cbi , cobinamide ; AdoCbi , adenosylcobinamide ; AdoCbi-P , adenosylcobinamide phosphate ; AdoCbi-GDP , adenosylcobinamide-GDP ; AdoCbl , adenosylcobalamin ; AdoCby , adenosylcobyric acid ; AP-P , R-1-aminopropanol-O-2-phosphate ; Me2Bza , 5,6-dimethylbenzimidazole .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10869342" target="_blank">10869342</a>]<br></li>
<li>3 The abbreviations used are : Cbl , cobalamin ; AdoCbl , adenosylcobalamin ; HOCbl , hydroxocobalamin ; CHES , 2 - ( cyclohexylamino ) ethanesulfonic acid ; CHAPS , 3 - [ ( 3-cholamidopro-pyl ) dimethylammonio ] -1 - propanesulfonic acid ; PPPi , inorganic tripolyphosphate .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16636051" target="_blank">16636051</a>]<br></li>
<li>31P NMR spectra of reference AdoCbi-P , adenosylcobinamide phosphate ; AdoCbl , adenosylcobalamin ; MeCbl , methylcobalamin ; L-Thr , L-threonine ; L-Thr-P , L-threonine-O-3-phosphate .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18308727" target="_blank">18308727</a>]<br></li>
<li>2 The abbreviations used are : AdoCbl , adenosylcobalamin ; Cby , cobyric acid ; L-Thr-P , L-threonine-O-3-phosphate ; GHMP , galactokinase , homoserine kinase , mevalonate kinase , and phosphomevalonate kinase ; AMP-PNP , ad-enylyl imidodiphosphate ; CD , circular dichroism ; 1,2-PD , 1,2-propanediol .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19509296" target="_blank">19509296</a>]<br></li>
